		" 
			>
			<DIV>I havent read the January Summit board yet, but I intend to after finally noticing that the title to this article implies that soloing may get some attention.&nbsp; That would be nice.&nbsp; Yes, very nice indeed.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>LDoN points for tasks may be&nbsp;going&nbsp;a bit far.&nbsp; The general philosopy is that the number of people required to get something determines its power.&nbsp; Solo tasks would allow one person to get the same gear it took at least 3 to get before.&nbsp; And that would be bad mmm-kay?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Summoning is obviously a huge issue.&nbsp; My suggestion is (and has always been) to give more mobs ranged attacks (knives, bows, rocks, balls of compressed kitten) and to make the AI of non-animal, non-undead (as if undead needed another prefix) smarter.&nbsp; Then relieve them of their summoning ability under heavy sedation.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I&nbsp;have many tips and suggestions, but&nbsp;alas too many hours working on my "Predator" have wiped me out.&nbsp; More later.</DIV>	
