		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I think that there should be Wandering Task Masters as well... Perhaps 1 per continent</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Scripted to spend an hour wandering randomly in a zone, then randomly warping to any non-city adjacent zone.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Make them completely factionless. Graphically, just an old man in a cloak.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And they give out their own sets of Tasks (still in the Task system, but unusual tasks).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Find a guy, get a task, do it, then you gotta find him again.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Should never go near a city and never go into a dungeon.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Hehe, my mind can think of 100's of storyline opportunities - some that could even be incorporated into the tasks themselves, revealing lore based on the tasks performed (similar to the lore related to the Adventurer's Stone, but necessary to the game)... For example, they could be collecting intelligence (spying) on our world in prepration for a coming invasion. Tasks might appear simple and benign, but...</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							- There is no such thing as a train, only challenging pulls.<br>- Never get into a battle of wits with an unarmed man.<br>- MGB Max Extended True North at FV stone in 5 minutes! No level restrictions - HURRY!!!<br>- Try  <a href='/eq/search?advanced=true' class="searchbar_text">Searching</a>,  it's fun, fast and free!<br>- "I will nerf this" - <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=119492#M119492" target="_BLANK">Absor</a
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
