<DIV></DIV>
<P>Ummm forgive me if i was wrong, but i was under the impression that the rewards the adv merchants gave were for doing work for em, not becuase you killed a certain mob or whatever.&nbsp; and lets say for a second that someone did a quest for adv points. Currently i am level 68 and when we do ldons we get 104 points for completion. which would take me roughly 14 ldons to get one peice of armor. Now if we set it at 1/6th the level i get now, well say that would mean i get 18 points per adv. So lets take a look at this it would mean that i would have to&nbsp;84 quests to get that same peice of armor. at roughly 1 hour per adv, or quest it would mean that im doing 84 hours of "work for adventurers" on quests and 14 hours of work for adv on ldon. what is the problem with someone being able to earn points that way, in what way would it unbalance things?</P>
