<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=49184#M49184">35</a> of 66
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 276 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Getting away from the LDoN point debate for a second, I'd like to see some soloing-specific content.  I'm thinking an outdoor zone with a variety of different level mobs, with room to kite.  The mob levels should scale accordingly as you get further in.<br><br>So, for example, maybe a instanced zone (so no kill stealing) that's long and somewhat narrow.  The zone walls would be safe for traveling (so you can easily get to the level mobs you want).  Mobs would have a low aggro range and don't summon.  You could pull to the zone edge and kite them there.<br><br>Or, perhaps an instanced zone where the type of mob depends on who requests the zone.  For example, a necro would get a zone filled with undead, a druid would get animals, mages would get summoned mobs, etc.  The mob placement and layout of the zone wouldn't change, just the "marker" for the type of mob.  You'd have to research this a little, but doing it that way might be enough so you could have summoning mobs... as a necro, I know if I can slow them, it doesn't matter if they summon.<br><br>This could actually help with grouping too - if you can't get a shaman for slows, get a necro and recieve an undead expedition.  Viola!	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
