		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Hmmm... one more comment on soloing.<br><br>If the goal is so all classes can more-or-less solo, then there's certain changes that must be made.  Soloing is made up from at least one of two components:<br><br>1) Snare.  The ability to slow a mob's run speed enough that you can get enough distance to cast a spell.<br>2) Slow.  The ability to slow a mob's attack speed enough that is it possible to tank it.<br><br>All successful soloing classes can do one or both of these things.  I was going to add "quick kill" to the list (which is how magician's solo), but once you're past level 60 or so, this simply isn't possible anymore.<br><br>Anyway, if the goal is allow more classes to solo, then one of these abilities must be added to everyone's skills.  You could make it mob-specific, such as magicians only slowing (or snaring) summoned mobs.<br><br>I'm not sure I agree that all classes should be able to solo, but since this is a thread about soloing, I felt it should at least be mentioned here.	
