<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=49196#M49196">37</a> of 66
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 270 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<P><STRONG>TAKEN FROM A POST OF MINE ON ANOTHER THREAD (I thought this should be here instead):</STRONG></P>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>A single player of any level, class or race should be able to do these things (among others):</P>
<UL>
<LI><U><FONT color=#999999>Gain experience </FONT></U><FONT color=#999999>at a reasonable pace, through a wide selection of enemies. </FONT>
<LI><U><FONT color=#999999>Complete a new quest </FONT></U><FONT color=#999999>with a meaningful reward upon completion. Note that it doesnt have to be *very* meaningful. </FONT>
<LI><U><FONT color=#999999>Advance a tradeskill </FONT></U><FONT color=#999999>to the same degree of skill as any other, and have its use not heavily tied to groups or raids. </FONT>
<LI><U><FONT color=#999999>Be able to explore </FONT></U><FONT color=#999999>and gain information, to a degree depending on class, newly published content of appropriate level for the purpose of hunting there. Exploration alone should not carry frustrating levels of risk. </FONT>
<LI><FONT color=#999999>Occasionally undertake and significantly <U>progress in a large, involved quest,</U> that may contain group and raid content.</FONT></LI></UL>
<P>I warn you that some of the above are subject to debate, but only stated as my opinion. </P>
<P>So finally, the answer to your question:</P>
<UL>
<LI>There is not enough soloable content above level 50 with a reasonable experience reward. 
<LI>There are not enough solo quests above level 50 with meaningful monetary, faction or item rewards. 
<LI>Tradeskilled items above 200 (especially PoP) require too many group or higher drops to create. 
<LI>Summoning and AE spell nerfs (as a solution to kiting) should be reworked, suggestions: 
<UL>
<LI>Inform the player upon targetting or considering that a creature can summon. 
<LI>Reduce the number of summoning creatures and give them ranged attacks to compensate. 
<LI>Improve the AI of chasing creatures with good intelligence (non-animal or undead). 
<LI>Provide a resistance check to summoning and/or a spell or ability to counter it. 
<LI>Improve collision tracking so that creatures cannot stack on top of one another.</LI></UL>
<LI>Adjust the XP system to better reflect the balance of the encounter. Challenging enemies should be rewarded with experience regardless of the number of participants, conversely trivial enemies should provide no experience. 
<LI>One long term Prayer Shawl style quest for each class should be included with each expansion. The result should be a single item of appropriate reward (armor quests dont count here).</LI></UL>
<P>All too much to ask for I suspect.</P>
<P>
<HR>
</P></DIV>
<P>To clarify on the XP system, can solo and pairs be made to be considered (for XP purposes) a different balance level than a full group?</P>
<P>I propose adding an EQ II style&nbsp;"balance level" to creature information (for considering and xp reward)&nbsp;in addition to class level (which would be for the purposes of resists, spells and abilities).&nbsp; The balance levels would be solo, group and raid.&nbsp; </P>
<P>This is a smaller change to game balance than some might think, which would allow the devs to create creatures designed for soloing without having groups abuse them for easy XP grinding.&nbsp; Also it would allow the XP award for raids to be increased (or not as the designers choose), which I feel would be a huge boon to the game.</P>
<P>Also, perhaps 2 people could "solo" together, splitting XP and reward while still being considered soloing for balance.&nbsp; The "solo"&nbsp;level of balance&nbsp;would have to take this into account.&nbsp;</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>12-13-2004</span> <span class=time_text>08:34 AM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
