<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Valdimear_Eci wrote:<BR>Hmmm... one more comment on soloing.<BR><BR>If the goal is so all classes can more-or-less solo, then there's certain changes that must be made. Soloing is made up from at least one of two components:<BR><BR>1) Snare. The ability to slow a mob's run speed enough that you can get enough distance to cast a spell.<BR>2) Slow. The ability to slow a mob's attack speed enough that is it possible to tank it.<BR><BR>All successful soloing classes can do one or both of these things. I was going to add "quick kill" to the list (which is how magician's solo), but once you're past level 60 or so, this simply isn't possible anymore.<BR><BR>Anyway, if the goal is allow more classes to solo, then one of these abilities must be added to everyone's skills. You could make it mob-specific, such as magicians only slowing (or snaring) summoned mobs.<BR><BR>I'm not sure I agree that all classes should be able to solo, but since this is a thread about soloing, I felt it should at least be mentioned here.<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Not true at all...</P>
<P>You can BUY (or even farm) Snare devices. They are even instant-cast. I am a necro and have my own snare, yet I carry a bunch of them. if MY snare is resisted, I can RClick the device (a fungus gland of some sort) on the run, trying to re-establish the snare. Other people I know use them as well to aggro kite - classes that cannot snare, like Chanters and Mages. Yes, they farm the glands in FG.</P>
<P>Alternatively, you can speed up the toon (admittedly, with the ridiculous speeds of the MOBs, this does not work in OoW) using SoW potions, mounts, RUN5, etc. Many people do this.</P>
<P>I have never used slow soloing as a Necro (we don't have it anyway).</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>As for instanced soloing areas, I doubt we could ever see them. If every single soloer required its own instance, and you made the zone solo-capable for every class, the hardware requirements to support it could get pretty extreme.</P>
