		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>Valdimear_Eci wrote:<BR>Hmmm... one more comment on soloing.<BR><BR>If the goal is so all classes can more-or-less solo, then there's certain changes that must be made. </P>
<P>
<HR>
</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Classes still have all the tools they need to solo, the only problem is the amount of summoning mobs..The easiest fix to bring back any type of soloing is to re-evaluate what mobs and amount of mobs that can summon a PC.</P>
<P>Adding abilities to classes to leviate the ability to solo could be to imbalancing to the game and/or other classes and then would lead to further discussions, arguments and all out whines and gripes.</P>
<P>As a necro, i would solo when ever i wasnt doing anything, more times have i been asked by someone if they could join me during my solo times then i have been asked to join a group...So in otherwords, grouping was easier when classes could solo pretty much everywhere.Solo turned into someone asking to join up, then he/her would&nbsp;seen how fun it was and a friend of either showed up, then someone else in zone asked and walla, before you know it i wasnt soloing anymore but a group had formed out of 1 persons ability to solo..friends were made, times were fun.</P>
<P>Now its seems your either in a group, or your LFG.. in laymens terms &lt; spellling &gt; getting xp or not getting xp.</P>
<P>There is also less interaction between players now as most stick with their usual groups, you also see alot more boxed characters now &lt; maybe due to people leaving and friends using their accounts &gt; but i tend to think its due to the fact its hard to find groups and even harder to solo for any decent amount of xp.&lt; except a few places fire/vxed etc &gt;</P>
<P>Some classes will always be able to solo, some will have a very hard time at it or not even be able to solo..Just like some classes will always have a hard time getting groups and some classes are always needed in groups...</P>
<P>I met more people, made more friends, and had alot more fun in the game when i could solo most of the content, now as i am forced to group more i am finding myself playing less everyday.<BR></P>
<DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
