<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=49360#M49360">42</a> of 66
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 250 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			These are some good discussions and I like a lot of the ideas I hear.<br><br>However....<br><br>One thing that concerns me is the idea that adding more solo content is a fix for people having trouble finding a group.  If SOE were to follow through with that idea, we'd all be playing Fable.  Solo content is important, there will always be times when one cannot get a group or doesn't have enough time, but it should always be more efficient to group than to solo.<br><br>Rather than attempt to fix grouping problems by adding more and better rewards for solo contet, SOE should look for ways for groups to get togehter faster, hunt faster, and offer ways to help people leave a group when they need to without harming themselves or the group.<br><br>As far as tasks go I would like to see the following things:<br><br>- Turn the task system into the quest journal for EQ.  Add a lot of older quests to the task system.  Allow people to select more than one task at a time.<br><br>- Offer item rewards for tasks.<br><br>- Use the task system as motivation for exploration.  Offer more tasks that send players around from landmark to landmark.  In the early levels, this can do a lot to help players expand out into those unused zones we all complain about.<br><br>- Add group tasks intended for somewhere between 3 and 6 people.  The leader picks a task sort of like an expedition and the group completes the task within 30 to 90 minutes.<br><br>- Fix any solo-friendly task that requires killing more than 10 mobbos.  Some of the tasks I attempted with my cleric, rogue, and berskerker (all different levels) took far longer than 90 minutes simply because I had to kill between 20 and 30 mobs.<br><br>- I like the idea of LDON tasks offering points, but it should always be more efficient to get a group together and go into the dungeons.  Offer perhaps half of the points they would normally get for the same amount of time.  60 minutes of hunting alone should give you 25 points at level 65 or above.<br><br>- Add in level 20 and level 40 armor quest tasks for a new set of nice armor at these levels.<br><br>- Add in level 40 "epic" tasks for a new epic-lite item doable with a single group at level 40.  The task can have a lot of steps and require a group to complete, but the task system is a perfect interface for such an event.<br><br>- Add in new task types other than collect, explore, kill, or hail. Add in tasks to slay one particular evil (not necessarily a rare spawn, but some sort of boss).<br><br>- Add in taskmasters in the newbie areas and add level 5 tasks so brand new players understand that the task system isn't just something to ignore but something they can continually work on throughout their career.<br><br>The task system has a lot of potential to bridge the gap between EQ1's bracket-based quest system and the EQ2 quest journal.  Instead of being a smaller feature of a single expansion, SOE could expand this system into a core line of progression from level 5 to 70.  The system itself seems to work just fine.  All it needs now are tweaks to existing content and new content.<br><br>Again, however, I don't want to see the task system being a solo-only system.  The fix for people who have trouble finding groups is to make it easier and faster to find groups, not to send them off by themselves.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Loral Ciriclight, Cleric of Tunare, Quellious<br><br><a href="mailto:loral@loralciriclight.com">loral@loralciriclight.com</a><br><br><a href="http://loralciriclight.com/">eq fiction</a> - <a href="http://loralciriclight.com/images/">images</a> - <a href="http://eqwire.com/">eq wire</a> - <a href="http://mobhunter.com/">mobhunter</a> - <a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/default.asp?column=8397">caster's realm</a> - <a href="http://loralciriclight.com/gear">gear</a>
