		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>I think we also need to get away from equating "soloing" from "solo hunting".</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>We have a lot of soloing capability and every class can do it, but we need more. Soloing is everything I can do without involving anybody else. It includes not only solo hunting, but tradeskills and a lot of quests.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I think there could be a LOT more.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I think of soloing, in part, as things to do while LFG. Sometimes soloing is a specific goal, sometimes it is just a hobby, sometimes a time sink while waiting for your guild raid to form, whatever. We just need even more.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>More tasks is a great step in that direction.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>[edit - add]</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Heck,&nbsp;scattering more vaiuable ground spawn around the world would be another step <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> Certainly would encourage people to wander around.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Say, for example, you made every zone drop an appropriately valuable (obviously Misty Thicket less than MPG) item if the zone has been empty for, say, 2 hours.</DIV><p>Message Edited by Klonn_Darkbane on <span class=date_text>12-14-2004</span> <span class=time_text>01:04 PM</span>
