		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I'd much prefer better ways to make groups, as I'll take a group over soloing almost every time.  Unfortunately, the game simply isn't made that way... some classes are extemely valuable in regards to grouping (like shamen, clerics) while others are much less so (necros, mages).<br><br>Ideally what I'd like to see is a necro, rogue, ranger, magician, wizard and beastlord be able to group together and go to the same kinds of places a warrior, cleric, shaman, and (pick two DPS classes here) could hunt at.  But honestly, I don't see that happening.  What I think would be possible is if *any* class can't get a group (regardless of the reason) they have a way to get experience.  Doesn't have to be a lot of experience, but forward progress nonetheless.  Tasks could be the answer.<br><br>Oh, and not to nitpick Klonn, but necros do have a slow, although against undead only.  It's a 30-something spell called Shackle of Spirit.  <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>	
